# ü´Ç nooneleftalone

> A real-time computer vision system that detects socially isolated individuals at events and nudges them back into the group ‚Äî because no one should be left alone.

---

## üìñ Project Description

**nooneleftalone** uses a live camera feed and YOLOv8 object detection to monitor social dynamics at events, parties, and gatherings. It identifies people who have been physically distant from others for too long, classifies them as isolated, and assigns them fun, low-pressure social tasks to help them re-engage ‚Äî all in real time.

---

## üõ† Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Backend | Python 3, Flask |
| Computer Vision | OpenCV (`cv2`), Ultralytics YOLOv8 (`yolov8n.pt`) |
| Frontend | HTML/Jinja2 Templates, JavaScript (polling `/stats`) |
| Video Streaming | Flask `multipart/x-mixed-replace` MJPEG stream |
| ML Model | YOLOv8n (nano) ‚Äî person detection only (class 0) |

---

## ‚ú® Features

- üéØ **Real-time Person Detection** ‚Äî Detects all people in the camera frame using YOLOv8, ignoring edge artefacts
- ‚è± **Isolation Timer** ‚Äî Tracks how long each person has been physically separated from the group using a configurable pixel-distance threshold
- üî¥ **3-State Visual Classification** ‚Äî Labels each person as `Engaged` (green), `Watching` (yellow countdown), or `LOW INTERACTION` (red alert)
- üìã **Dynamic Task Assignment** ‚Äî Assigns 3 randomized social re-engagement tasks to isolated individuals (e.g. "Introduce yourself to someone")
- üìä **Live Stats API** ‚Äî `/stats` endpoint streams real-time JSON data (total people, isolated count, per-person status) for frontend dashboards
- üéõ **Adjustable Distance Threshold** ‚Äî POST to `/set_distance` to tune the isolation sensitivity on the fly without restarting

## ‚öôÔ∏è Installation

```bash
# 1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/nooneleftalone.git
cd nooneleftalone

# 2. Create and activate a virtual environment
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate        # macOS/Linux
venv\Scripts\activate           # Windows

# 3. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

**requirements.txt** should include:
```
flask
opencv-python
ultralytics
```

> The YOLOv8 nano weights (`yolov8n.pt`) are downloaded automatically by Ultralytics on first run.

## üîå API Reference

| Route | Method | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `/` | GET | Main dashboard (video + stats UI) |
| `/video` | GET | MJPEG live camera stream |
| `/stats` | GET | JSON ‚Äî total people, isolated count, per-person status |
| `/start_camera` | POST | Initialize and start the webcam |
| `/stop_camera` | POST | Stop the webcam and reset state |
| `/set_distance` | POST | Update isolation pixel threshold ‚Äî body: `{"distance": 200}` |

**Example `/stats` response:**
```json
{
  "total": 4,
  "isolated": 1,
  "persons": [
    {
      "id": "P01",
      "status": "isolated",
      "elapsed": 23.4,
      "tasks": ["Introduce yourself to someone", "Give someone a compliment", "Take a group selfie"]
    }
  ]
}
```

**Data Flow:**
```

    ‚Üí Distance check per person

            ‚Üí Frame annotation (OpenCV draw)

```
